h","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Such a file in a CSV format would quickly become unwieldy. Furthermore, much of the data is “repeated.” That is, all the Denver station data has “DEN” in the station column. Over hundreds, or thousands, of data entries this redundant data can add up to unnecessarily large file size. In addition, this particular example does not have geospatial data.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"On9qrmwlie"}],"key":"yEolZkC7K7"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With Parquet, this data can be saved in a more storage-efficient format. GeoParquet extends Parquet to add geospatial/geometry data and metadata to Parquet data sets. An interested reader can read the introductory blog post with more detail ","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"XcNoYbLIHy"},{"type":"link","url":"https://xebia.com/blog/introducing-the-geoparquet-data-format/","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"dbdhAuuvIT"}],"urlSource":"https://xebia.com/blog/introducing-the-geoparquet-data-format/","key":"CYydYhPVfA"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"ogyfvRdxtA"}],"key":"oPtDNR8eFS"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The IEM provides a historical archive of global ASOS data in the native METAR format. To conclude our GeoParquet story, ","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"eqz2wtF0VE"},{"type":"link","url":"https://dynamical.org/catalog/asos-parquet/","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Dynamical.org","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"JBOweiJnwj"}],"urlSource":"https://dynamical.org/catalog/asos-parquet/","key":"sbDYfLOIz0"},{"type":"text","value":" has created a processing pipeline that takes raw METAR from the IEM, transforms it into the GeoParquet format, and makes it readily available via the internet.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"ItHpMDImVz"}],"key":"sEgyli3AGA"}],"key":"aBm7PmdlGq"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-content","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"🦆 The What, Why, and How of DuckDB 🦆","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"ZdMpfDSzaG"}],"identifier":"id-the-what-why-and-how-of-duckdb","label":"🦆 The What, Why, and How of DuckDB 🦆","html_id":"id-the-what-why-and-how-of-duckdb","implicit":true,"key":"WnsZcwvYrb"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"Hyy9buwjVu"},{"type":"link","url":"https://duckdb.org/why_duckdb","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"DuckDB","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"ldyhMQfVtH"}],"urlSource":"https://duckdb.org/why_duckdb","key":"npcha3Dcbl"},{"type":"text","value":" is a relational (table-oriented) DBMS [(Database Management System)] that supports the Structured Query Language (SQL).”","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"MqR9F4FsU3"}],"key":"ARyP3vf2OM"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"childr